      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=n9ud5ZPu2Po" target="_blank"
        >Mammals - Traits and Groups of Warm-Blooded Animals (Video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=mXs71vqrvqI" target="_blank"
        >Vertebrate Diversity in Mammals (General Characteristics) (video)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5900">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 2. </span>
      Explain how the animal kingdom is classified. Explain where mammals fit in
      the classification of animals. Classify three mammals from phylum through
      species. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
      <a href="https://youtu.be/oID1h-zL-uw?si=jHkAIYYgKaxKTZwG" target="_blank"
        >The 5 Kingdoms in Classification (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/L6anmd7DnYw?si=tVuoSQOwEYpKbYO7" target="_blank"
        >Animal Classification (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a href="https://youtu.be/YAgjPwiSbvA?si=gwU-5Y3dVcmjt8Z7" target="_blank"
        >The Three Types of Mammals, Differences, and How to Tell (video)</a
      ><br />
      <a
        href="https://www.departments.bucknell.edu/biology/resources/msw3/browse.asp"
        target="_blank"
        >Mammal Species of the World Database (website)</a
      >
    </div>
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5887">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 3. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5887 mb-requirement-id-5888">
        (a) Spend three hours in two different kinds of natural habitats or at
        different elevations for a total of 6 hours. List the different mammal
        species and how many of each you identified by sight or sign. Tell why
        all mammals do not live in the same kind of habitat. <br /><i
          >Resources:</i
        >
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=x8DfP0Nh7kA" target="_blank"
          >How to Find Mammal Signs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.greenbelly.co/pages/animal-tracks-identification-guide"
          target="_blank"
          >Animal Tracks Identification Guide | Animal Footprint ID Charts
          (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5887 mb-requirement-id-5889">
        (b) Spend three hours on five different days in at least a 25-acre area
        (about the size of 31/2 football fields) for a total of 15 hours. List
        the mammal species you identified by sight or sign.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5887 mb-requirement-id-5890">
        (c) From study and reading, write a simple life history of one nongame
        mammal that lives in your area. Tell how this mammal lived before its
        habitat was affected in any way by humans. Tell how it reproduces, what
        it eats, and its natural habitat. Describe its dependency upon plants
        and other animals (including humans), and how they depend upon it.
        Describe how humans have benefited from the mammal you have chosen and
        whether the mammal has benefited from association with humankind.
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
  </div>
  <div class="mb-requirement-item">
    <div class="mb-requirement-parent mb-requirement-id-5891">
      <span class="mb-requirement-listnumber"> 4. </span>
      Do ONE of the following:
    </div>
    <ul class="mb-requirement-children-list">
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5892">
        (a) Under the guidance of a nature center or natural history museum,
        make two study skins of rats or mice. Tell the uses of study skins and
        mounted specimens respectively. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/m93WO9praZE?si=DG3Wt7aD9EBE-Zma"
          target="_blank"
          >Skinning Your Rat (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=dBk9jwQBiuA" target="_blank"
          >Preparing Mammal Specimens (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5893">
        (b) Take good pictures of two kinds of mammals in the wild. Record the
        date(s), time of day, weather conditions, approximate distance from the
        animal, habitat conditions, and any other factors you feel may have
        influenced the animal's activity and behavior. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r5liiAoUJ1Q" target="_blank"
          >Top 10 Wildlife Photography Shortcuts (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=wzuxDkmsZgM" target="_blank"
          >The Most Important Wildlife Photography (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://photographylife.com/wildlife-photography-tutorial"
          target="_blank"
          >The Ultimate Wildlife Photography Tutorial (website)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.fs.usda.gov/visit/know-before-you-go/wildlife-photography"
          target="_blank"
          >Wildlife Photography (website)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5894">
        (c) Write a life history of a native game mammal that lives in your
        area, covering the points outlined in requirement 3(c). List sources for
        this information.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5895">
        (d) Make and bait a tracking pit. Report what mammals and other animals
        came to the bait. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=rjg7FUw_5fM" target="_blank"
          >Build Animal Track Station (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=j_SPxHCvSYA" target="_blank"
          >Creating a Backyard Animal Track Trap With Household Items (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=i2SFVKWhIzY" target="_blank"
          >Animal Tracking Basics - Track Traps, Measurements, Following Sign
          (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5896">
        (e) Visit a natural history museum. Report on how specimens are prepared
        and cataloged. Explain the purposes of museums. <br /><i>Resource:</i>
        <a
          href="https://youtu.be/sCm6JFBdWfM?si=abiHDMFT2hvlOGJS"
          target="_blank"
          >What Is the Purpose of a Natural History Museum? (video)</a
        >
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5897">
        (f) Write a report of 500 words on a book about a mammal species.
      </li>
      <li class="mb-requirement-child mb-parent-5891 mb-requirement-id-5898">
        (g) Trace two possible food chains of carnivorous mammals from the soil
        through four stages to the mammal. <br /><i>Resources:</i>
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=FpVXlk_Z-4E" target="_blank"
          >Animal of the Week: Food Chains (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=JCl_yDf0Qok" target="_blank"
          >Food Chains &amp; Food Webs (video)</a
        ><br />
        <a
          href="https://www.sciencefacts.net/tundra-food-chain.html"
          target="_blank"
          >Tundra Food Chain (website)</a
        >
      </li>
    </ul>
    <div style="padding-left: 10px; font-size: 14px; color: #515354"></div>
    <br />
